WEBVTT

00:00:34.803 --> 00:00:36.123
Who is it from?

00:00:36.773 --> 00:00:38.563
I can't guess from
the handwriting.

00:00:39.712 --> 00:00:41.003
M. Mitra

00:00:42.593 --> 00:00:44.403
Must be someone on your
mother's side.

00:00:45.874 --> 00:00:47.451
I don't know of any
M. Mitra.

00:01:03.209 --> 00:01:05.203
They say, there'll be no power
cuts during the holidays.

00:01:07.336 --> 00:01:09.283
Well? Who's it from?

00:01:22.745 --> 00:01:24.283
Whose letter is it, Mummy?

00:01:24.655 --> 00:01:26.003
- Just a moment.

00:01:26.443 --> 00:01:29.819
Ok. Like a massive...

00:01:33.265 --> 00:01:34.043
Well?

00:01:40.546 --> 00:01:43.003
Is it some bad news?

00:01:44.803 --> 00:01:45.803
I don't know.

00:01:46.972 --> 00:01:48.163
Don't know?

00:01:50.202 --> 00:01:51.723
Who's that from, Mummy?

00:01:53.803 --> 00:01:55.283
Your great uncle!

00:01:56.612 --> 00:01:58.588
The one who ran away
from home?

00:01:58.665 --> 00:02:00.323
But he's been missing
for ages!

00:02:01.803 --> 00:02:05.239
35 years! He left in 1955.

00:02:06.483 --> 00:02:08.083
I was only two then.

00:02:08.759 --> 00:02:09.923
And your uncle?

00:02:11.765 --> 00:02:13.763
He left immediately
after graduation.

00:02:15.119 --> 00:02:16.763
I don't remember him at all.

00:02:18.888 --> 00:02:20.883
Later, my mother told me
everything.

00:02:23.572 --> 00:02:25.763
Last time we heard from him
was in 1968.

00:02:26.535 --> 00:02:29.763
He never wrote to any of his
relatives.

00:02:30.763 --> 00:02:34.324
Only to Mr. Sital. A post
cover every 6 months or so.

00:02:34.606 --> 00:02:37.003
From various places in Europe.

00:02:38.334 --> 00:02:41.083
It was not possible to reply
because he gave no address.

00:02:41.613 --> 00:02:45.003
This Sital was a family friend,
wasn't he?

00:02:46.280 --> 00:02:48.172
Yes.
He was grandpa's neighbour.

00:02:48.249 --> 00:02:49.923
He has been to see us also.

00:02:51.477 --> 00:02:56.403
Oh yes. He was in the
Governor's accounts department.

00:02:56.808 --> 00:02:58.723
He has retired and is living in
Shanti Niketan, isn't it?

00:03:00.402 --> 00:03:02.403
It was from him that
uncle learnt about us.

00:03:02.683 --> 00:03:03.763
Where has he written from?

00:03:05.018 --> 00:03:05.923
New Delhi.

00:03:07.834 --> 00:03:09.163
Qutub Hotel.

00:03:18.071 --> 00:03:20.643
Any way, just read me
the letter, will you?

00:03:22.923 --> 00:03:26.403
I must say his command of
Bengali is admirable.

00:03:28.490 --> 00:03:30.142
My dear Baby.

00:03:30.219 --> 00:03:32.403
Baby? Who is baby?

00:03:32.849 --> 00:03:34.923
Let me read it, will you?

00:03:37.059 --> 00:03:38.861
My dear Baby.

00:03:38.938 --> 00:03:40.812
I don't know your real name.

00:03:40.970 --> 00:03:43.243
Oh! I'm addressing you
in this fashion.

00:03:43.320 --> 00:03:44.923
I hope you won't mind.

00:03:45.694 --> 00:03:47.323
That's very florid style.

00:03:48.393 --> 00:03:52.403
When I left home, you were
no more than a baby.

00:03:52.479 --> 00:03:55.217
I have finished my travels
in the West...

00:03:55.294 --> 00:03:57.403
... and have only just
arrived here.

00:03:57.633 --> 00:04:01.303
... learnt from
Mr. Sital that...

00:04:01.485 --> 00:04:04.923
... you're my only
close relation left...

00:04:05.778 --> 00:04:09.923
... and are settled happily.
Your husband and son ...

00:04:10.403 --> 00:04:14.403
I shall soon resume
my wanderings.

00:04:14.923 --> 00:04:18.232
In the meantime,
I dearly wish...

00:04:18.309 --> 00:04:20.915
to spend a week as the
guest of my niece...

00:04:21.063 --> 00:04:23.523
... in the city of
my birth.

00:04:24.302 --> 00:04:26.810
Won't know this uncle
of yours by sight...

00:04:26.887 --> 00:04:28.683
... as I won't know you.

00:04:29.135 --> 00:04:31.363
I realize that in the
instances my request...

00:04:31.440 --> 00:04:33.923
... amounts to an
imposition.

00:04:34.241 --> 00:04:37.923
In our country,
in the old days, ...

00:04:38.201 --> 00:04:40.817
...hospitality was
extended even...

00:04:41.083 --> 00:04:43.923
... to total strangers.

00:04:44.570 --> 00:04:46.829
It is the thought
of this tradition...

00:04:46.906 --> 00:04:50.243
... that gives me the courage
to make this request.

00:04:50.403 --> 00:04:51.918
I have decided.

00:04:51.995 --> 00:04:55.403
We leave by the Rajdhani
Express on the 16th ...

00:04:55.479 --> 00:04:58.403
... and arrive in Calcutta
on the 17th morning.

00:04:58.479 --> 00:05:01.516
I shall then turn up at
your house in a taxi.

00:05:02.098 --> 00:05:04.923
It is certainly up to you
to accept me...

00:05:05.128 --> 00:05:08.403
...as a guest or not.

00:05:08.807 --> 00:05:09.870
Let me assure you.

00:05:09.947 --> 00:05:15.403
I'm used to experiences
both bitter and sweet.

00:05:15.838 --> 00:05:17.341
Yours affectionately, ...

00:05:17.418 --> 00:05:20.283
Uncle Manmohan Mitra.

00:05:21.403 --> 00:05:23.923
You have no memories
of your uncle.

00:05:24.723 --> 00:05:27.923
You even recall whether he is
stout or thin or tall or short.

00:05:29.723 --> 00:05:30.403
No.

00:05:31.787 --> 00:05:35.923
So there is only one thing.
Send an immediate reply...

00:05:36.403 --> 00:05:38.483
... by telegram,
A letter won't do.

00:05:51.647 --> 00:05:54.063
Tell him a bare faced lie?

00:05:54.778 --> 00:05:56.222
What do you mean a lie?

00:05:56.371 --> 00:05:58.243
That people go on holidays...?

00:05:58.403 --> 00:06:00.403
... doesn't know
I'm an executive...

00:06:00.979 --> 00:06:02.403
... as if I were a professor?

00:06:02.723 --> 00:06:04.633
We are enjoying a long holiday
on autumn, wouldn't I?

00:06:04.710 --> 00:06:06.592
That you're not professor.

00:06:06.800 --> 00:06:09.403
How can you be sure that
this man isn't lying?

00:06:09.563 --> 00:06:11.683
You know how common fraud
is these days?

00:06:12.720 --> 00:06:15.323
There's a priceless art collection...

00:06:15.600 --> 00:06:19.826
... in that sitting room alone.
Subjects worth a million rupees.

00:06:20.540 --> 00:06:22.123
Take just one bronze
figurine...

00:06:22.683 --> 00:06:24.657
.... from the top
of the book shelf...

00:06:24.733 --> 00:06:25.923
... and you can make
a fortune...

00:06:26.000 --> 00:06:27.323
... by selling it to a
foreign tourist.

00:06:29.474 --> 00:06:31.403
You mean he is coming
to commit a theft

00:06:36.256 --> 00:06:38.643
Uncle was a great
favourite of my mother.

00:06:39.137 --> 00:06:40.923
Dad too was very fond on him.

00:06:41.993 --> 00:06:43.447
Did not without reason.

00:06:43.679 --> 00:06:45.058
Uncle was very gifted.

00:06:45.522 --> 00:06:47.403
Never stood second in his life.

00:06:51.866 --> 00:06:55.619
Here a person can change
beyond recognition.

00:06:56.358 --> 00:06:58.123
It doesn't seem so
from the letter.

00:07:00.667 --> 00:07:03.639
I'll assume that he is
indeed your uncle...

00:07:04.013 --> 00:07:05.603
... and a model of virtue.

00:07:06.188 --> 00:07:08.563
Won't you give your husband
a little thought?

00:07:09.675 --> 00:07:10.923
What do you mean?

00:07:16.093 --> 00:07:19.403
Says he's coming on
the 17th, Friday.

00:07:20.078 --> 00:07:21.756
That he'll stay for a week.

00:07:21.832 --> 00:07:24.683
Means, the whole weekend
would be ruined.

00:07:25.203 --> 00:07:27.403
The autumn festival
starts on 21st.

00:07:28.403 --> 00:07:30.365
I thought I'd relax
during the holidays.

00:07:30.631 --> 00:07:32.225
Now comes this old man...

00:07:32.549 --> 00:07:33.803
...claiming to be your uncle.

00:07:41.051 --> 00:07:43.923
Come in dear sir. Sit down in.
Have a meal dear, sir.

00:07:45.083 --> 00:07:46.264
Don't like it at all.

00:07:46.341 --> 00:07:47.483
What?

00:07:47.559 --> 00:07:49.243
Your attitude, what else?

00:07:49.403 --> 00:07:51.403
You can't send this telegram
in answer to this letter.

00:07:51.563 --> 00:07:54.403
As a thoroughly decent letter!
- I don't deny that.

00:07:55.547 --> 00:07:59.923
In fact, its a little too
decent. - That's the trouble.

00:08:00.121 --> 00:08:01.865
How can a man who's been
away from home so long...

00:08:01.942 --> 00:08:03.923
... write such elegant Bengali?

00:08:05.403 --> 00:08:09.196
May be he got someone else
to write for him.

00:08:09.644 --> 00:08:10.923
But the sentiment is
surely his own.

00:08:11.000 --> 00:08:14.403
No. There's a snag in it.

00:08:18.504 --> 00:08:19.563
Very well.

00:08:24.923 --> 00:08:26.843
Is grand uncle coming, mummy?

00:08:28.832 --> 00:08:30.203
Ask Daddy.

00:08:35.158 --> 00:08:36.123
What is it now?

00:08:39.625 --> 00:08:40.963
Are you cross with me
or something?

00:08:55.508 --> 00:08:57.110
A fake uncle is better than
no uncle.

00:08:57.187 --> 00:09:00.923
Is that what you wish to say?
- Wish to say only one thing.

00:09:01.570 --> 00:09:03.923
What's the need for a
letter or a telegram?

00:09:04.123 --> 00:09:06.243
He says he is coming here
on the 17th.

00:09:06.320 --> 00:09:07.140
Let him come.

00:09:07.217 --> 00:09:08.577
If I find him a fake...

00:09:08.653 --> 00:09:10.354
... or is real, but has come
with an ulterior motive, ...

00:09:10.430 --> 00:09:12.683
... then you won't have
to do anything.

00:09:12.923 --> 00:09:14.923
I'll myself whisk him
away with a broom.

00:09:19.105 --> 00:09:22.923
Just think - a fake
great uncle!

